?><h2>How to create Facebook application</h2>
<p>You will need a Facebook <b>Application ID</b> before you start using the feature.</p>
<p>Create a new app on the <a target="_blank" href="http://developers.facebook.com/apps/">Facebook App Dashboard</a>, and enter your app's basic information.</p>
<center><img src="https://fbcdn-dragon-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-ash3/851558_608093449202580_1445287580_n.PNG" alt="" /></center>
<p>Once you've created the app, note the app ID shown at the top of the dashboard page.</p>
<center><img src="https://fbcdn-dragon-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-prn1/851565_609147282448177_1169536347_n.PNG" alt="" /></center>
<p>You can see a special secret value is automatically generated for it. Please, put both <b>Application ID</b> and <b>Application Secret</b> into appropriate inputs in the Facebook login configuration options.</p>
<p>Now you're all set and ready to use login with Facebook account feature.</p>
<p>Find more information about Facebook Login for Websites in the <a target="_blank" href="https://developers.facebook.com/docs/facebook-login/overview/">official documentation</a>.</p>